commitResults.messageTitle: Fix test failures related to EditCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
Changes made to the ModelManager class resulted in testcase
failures. This commit rectifies them by editing the EditCommand
class to update the filtered list appropriately in the model on
execution.

EditCommand was erroneously edited to take personType as a parameter
in the previous commits. Its syntax and implementation remain an issue,
but the errors have been undone at surface level for now.

DeleteCommand was being parsed with a personType, which is unused in
implementation. To resolve this, ParserBasic and ParserComplex classes
have been written to better suit the needs as well as aid in testing.
- Basic commands do not require specifying personType
- Complex commands require a personType tag
It is very likely that we will add more basic commands in the future as
well, for example changing user settings, exporting data etc.

Also fix some bugs with the parsing of different command Patterns
- Previously Basic commands could also be parsed as Complex
- This has been fixed by altering the Complex command regex to be more
restrictive.
Implement FindCommand to search using prefixes

commitResults.messageBody:
Change find command so that it does a substring search for
certain parameters that are inconvenient to query by whole words.

Specifically:
- Name (Searching by short forms of long names)
- Email (Searching for emails without having to type out domain
names)
- Location (Searching for long addresses made easier)
- Phone (Searching for people by phone possible even if the
whole phone number is not memorised)
Improve find command flexibility
